---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy"
  description="How Pro City Laser Removal collects, uses, and protects your personal data, and how we use cookies on this website."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-neutral-mid mb-8">
      <ol class="flex gap-2">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-dark transition-colors">Home</a></li>
        <li aria-hidden="true">›</li>
        <li aria-current="page" class="text-on-surface">Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-mid">Last updated: July 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-12 text-on-surface">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Who we are</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          Pro City Laser Removal is a UK-based specialist laser cleaning company. We are the data
          controller for personal data collected through this website (procitylasers.com).
        </p>
        <dl class="text-sm space-y-2">
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <dt class="text-neutral-mid w-36 shrink-0">Contact email</dt>
            <dd><a href="mailto:info@procitylasers.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">info@procitylasers.com</a></dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <dt class="text-neutral-mid w-36 shrink-0">Phone</dt>
            <dd><a href="tel:+447878261529" class="hover:underline">07878 261529</a></dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <dt class="text-neutral-mid w-36 shrink-0">ICO registration</dt>
            <dd class="text-neutral-mid">[ICO registration number — to be confirmed]</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">What data we collect</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          We only collect personal data that you provide voluntarily through the enquiry form on
          this website. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm mb-3">
          <li>Your name</li>
          <li>Your company or organisation (optional)</li>
          <li>Your email address</li>
          <li>A description of your project</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-mid">
          We do not collect sensitive personal data, payment information, or data from third-party
          sources.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">How we use your data</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">We use your enquiry data to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm mb-4">
          <li>Respond to your enquiry</li>
          <li>Prepare and send a quote or project proposal</li>
          <li>Carry out any work you subsequently commission</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">
          <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Legitimate interests — responding to business enquiries is
          a necessary part of running our business and is what you would reasonably expect when
          submitting a contact form. Where a project proceeds, the basis becomes performance of
          a contract.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-mid">
          We do not use your data for unsolicited marketing, pass it to third parties for their
          own marketing, or make automated decisions based on it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">How long we keep your data</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Enquiry data is retained for up to three years from the date of your enquiry, or for
          the duration of any business relationship, whichever is longer. After that period,
          data is deleted unless we have a legal obligation to keep it (for example, for tax
          or accounting purposes, where the retention period is seven years).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Data processors</h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
          We use the following third-party services to operate this website. Each acts as a
          data processor under our instruction.
        </p>
        <div class="border border-neutral-light overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-neutral-light border-b border-neutral-light">
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-dark">Service</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-dark">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-dark">Location</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-neutral-light">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Netlify</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">Website hosting and form processing</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">USA (SCCs in place)</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-mid mt-3">
          SCCs = Standard Contractual Clauses, the approved mechanism for transferring personal
          data from the UK to countries outside the UK and EEA.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Cookies</h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
          A cookie is a small text file stored on your device. This website uses a small number
          of cookies, described below. We do not use advertising or tracking cookies.
        </p>

        <div class="border border-neutral-light overflow-x-auto mb-4">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-neutral-light border-b border-neutral-light">
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-dark">Name / Type</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-dark">Category</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-dark">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-medium text-neutral-dark">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-neutral-light">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">cookie_consent<br/><span class="text-neutral-mid font-sans normal-case">(localStorage)</span></td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">Strictly necessary</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">Stores your cookie preference so we do not ask again</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">Until browser storage is cleared</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-neutral-light">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Netlify functional</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">Strictly necessary</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">Enables form submissions and protects against spam and DDoS attacks</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-mid">Session or short-term</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-mid">
          We do not currently use analytics, advertising, or social media cookies. If this
          changes, this policy will be updated before any new cookies are set.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-dark mt-6 mb-3">Managing cookies</h3>
        <p class="text-sm mb-3">
          You can change your cookie preference at any time by clicking the button below. You
          can also delete cookies and browser storage through your browser settings — refer to
          your browser's help pages for instructions.
        </p>
        <button
          id="reset-consent"
          type="button"
          class="text-sm border border-accent text-accent px-4 py-2 hover:bg-accent hover:text-surface transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
        >
          Change my cookie preference
        </button>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Your rights</h2>
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm">
          Under UK GDPR you have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm mb-4">
          <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — ask us to delete your data where there is no legitimate reason to keep it</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong> — ask us to pause processing of your data in certain circumstances</li>
          <li><strong>Objection</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
          <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm">
          To exercise any of these rights, email{' '}
          <a href="mailto:info@procitylasers.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">
            info@procitylasers.com
          </a>.
          We will respond within one month.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Complaints</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          If you believe we have handled your data incorrectly, you have the right to lodge a
          complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), the UK supervisory
          authority for data protection.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
          <a
            href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/"
            class="text-accent hover:underline"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="Make a complaint to the ICO (opens in new tab)"
          >
            ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-mid">
          We would always prefer to resolve any concern directly — please contact us first.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-dark mb-4">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">
          We may update this policy when our practices change (for example, if we add
          analytics). The date at the top of the page shows when it was last updated. We will
          not make material changes without updating the cookie consent banner if it affects
          the cookies we use.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<script>
  document.getElementById('reset-consent')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    localStorage.removeItem('cookie_consent');
    document.documentElement.classList.remove('cookie-consent-given');
    window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
  });
</script>
